post_text:
Parenting Series: Raising Great Kids in a Challenging World

The LHCSD Counseling Department this year invites parents of ALL students to join us for our new parent night series. We will talk about everything from supporting your child’s academic success to instilling a strong sense of self. This parenting series is designed to offer practical solutions for parents of students of all ages. The first presentation on Cyber Safety took place at Washington Middle School’s Multi-Purpose Room on Thursday, September 26. Thank you to the Orange County Sheriff’s Department for their presentation to our families on the importance of Internet safety. We look forward to our parents and guardians participating in the upcoming parent nights. The location will be forthcoming for the October 16 meeting.

post_text: It is that time again for La Habra City School District schools to participate in International Walk to School Day 2019! This year's Walk to School Day was a huge success. International Walk to School Day is a global event that involves communities from more than 40 countries walking and biking to school on the same day. It began in 1997 as a one-day event. Over time, this event has become part of a movement for year-round safe routes to school and a celebration – with record-breaking participation – each October. Today, thousands of schools across America – from all 50 states, the District of Columbia, and Puerto Rico – participate every October (UNC Highway Safety Research Center, 2019).

post_text:
Arbolita Elementary School, A Visual and Performing Arts Academy, hosts its First Annual Arbolita Arts Festival.

What a night, what a show! Arbolita students and staff put on an amazing display of Visual and Performing Arts for the La Habra Community. The first annual Visual and Performing Arts (VAPA) Festival was the culmination of many months of teaching, learning, planning and preparation to welcome parents and community members to Arbolita to enjoy student performances.

With the reconfiguration of La Habra City School District, Arbolita was selected to become the District’s first ever VAPA focused magnet. One year later Arbolita Elementary has greatly transformed, offering piano lab classes, chorus, Disney Musicals, and collaboration with The Kennedy Center, Any Given Child. A very special guest in attendance was Cathy Rigby, former Olympic Gymnast, actor and motivational speaker. Congratulations to the Arbolita students, parents and staff for a great night!
#lhcsd #1team1vision #VAPA
http://bit.ly/2XgxMUh

post_text:
Good afternoon La Habra City School District families. This is Dr. Joanne Culverhouse.
This morning at approximately 10:00 a.m., the La Habra Police Department placed Walnut, El Cerrito, and Arbolita Schools on lockdown as a precautionary measure. The situation did not occur on our campuses; and has been resolved. Walnut, El Cerrito, and Arbolita schools have resumed their normal school activities, and all students and staff are safe. Thank you for your continued support and have a good Memorial Day weekend.

Buenos tardes familias del Distrito Escolar de La Habra. Este es un mensaje en nombre de la Doctora Joanne Culverhouse. Aproximadamente a las 10:00 am., el Departamento de Policía de La Habra tomó medidas de precaución y cerraron las escuelas Walnut, El Cerrito y Arbolita. La situación no ocurrió en ninguna de nuestras escuelas y ha sido resuelta. Walnut, El Cerrito y Arbolita han regresado a sus actividades escolares normales, y todos los estudiantes y el personal están seguros. Gracias por su apoyo continuo y tengan un buen fin de semana conmemorativo.

post_text: Good morning, Yesterday evening the La Habra Police Department received information regarding a potential threat at La Habra High School. After investigating, the La Habra Police department has concluded that the threat is not viable and is a hoax. However, as a precautionary measure, LHPD will have increased presence at all of the District’s sites today. The District and the La Habra Police Department are working together to keep our students safe.
text: Good morning, Yesterday evening the La Habra Police Department received information regarding a potential threat at La Habra High School. After investigating, the La Habra Police department has concluded that the threat is not viable and is a hoax. However, as a precautionary measure, LHPD will have increased presence at all of the District’s sites today. The District and the La Habra Police Department are working together to keep our students safe.

shared_text:
La Habra City School District
January 3, 2018 at 11:08 PM ·

R3 You Ready? It is time to Reconfigure, Redesign, and Revitalize our educational delivery system to meet the needs of our students and better prepare them for high school, college, careers, and beyond.

Please visit us at the La Habra Community Center on Wednesday January 17 from 4 p.m. - 7 p.m. or on Saturday January 20 from 9 a.m. - 12 p.m. to learn about the new opportunities coming to our District. You will have an opportunity to learn and ask questions about our Code to the Future, STEAM, VAPA, and International Baccalaureate candidacy programs as you prepare for the 2018 – 2019 school year.

Preview our Upcoming School Focuses before the R3 You Ready? Rally HERE - https://goo.gl/xiJ5yH

As you move around the community, you have probably sensed an exciting new “buzz” about La Habra City School District. We are on the MOVE!
